<div class="default-page">
  <div class="header">
    <h1 id="main-title" class="container">Praxent Watson Hackathon</h1>
    <h3 class="container">You're looking at: <code><%= view.pathFromApp + '.' +view.ext %></code></h3>
  </div>
  <div class="main container clearfix">
    <ul class="getting-started">
      <li class="clearfix">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sprite one"></div>
          <h3>
            Set up Watson integration.
          </h3>
          <p>
            We'll be using the <code>watson-developer-cloud</code> module to integrate with Watson.
            Watson environment variables will be set and accessed at <code>sails.config.watson</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="clearfix">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sprite two"></div>
          <h3>
            Integrate speech-to-text with tone analysis.
          </h3>
          <p>
            The user will <a href="/app">record their voice through their browser</a> which will stream to Watson to provide speech-to-text.
            Once the user has finished talking, we will run tone analysis using Watson and display the results.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="clearfix">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="sprite three"></div>
          <h3>
            Bonus points! Personality analysis with Twitter.
          </h3>
          <p>
            If we have time we can add personality analysis using Twitter.
            The user will log in through Twitter and Watson will read their feed and provide a personality analysis.
            We will use the <code>machinepack-twitter</code> module.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
